Turkey’s President Recep Tayyip Erdogan will make a visit to Iran on Monday for bilateral and trilateral summits with Iran’s President Ebrahim Raisi and Russia’s President Vladimir Putin. Erdogan will arrive in Tehran on Monday evening, heading a high-profile delegation. He will be accorded an official reception ceremony by President Raisi. They will appear before reporters after the one-on-one meeting. The Turkish president will attend the seventh meeting of the high committee of Iran-Turkey cooperation and the seventh summit of the Astana Format.